trans-unit.source: Represents an access control list (ACL) and is the base class for the <xref href="System.Security.AccessControl.DiscretionaryAcl"></xref> and <xref href="System.Security.AccessControl.SystemAcl"></xref> classes.
trans-unit.target: Representa uma lista de controle de acesso (ACL) e é a classe base para o <xref href="System.Security.AccessControl.DiscretionaryAcl"> </xref> e <xref href="System.Security.AccessControl.SystemAcl"> </xref> classes.

trans-unit.source: Certain combinations of inheritance and access mask flags are meaningless: - Any access control entry (ACE) with a zero-access mask is removed.
trans-unit.target: Algumas combinações de sinalizadores de máscara de acesso e herança não fazem sentidas:-qualquer entrada de controle de acesso (ACE) com uma máscara de acesso de zero é removida.

trans-unit.source: - Inherit-only ACEs inside object ACLs are removed.
trans-unit.target: -Somente herdada ACEs dentro de ACLs de objeto são removidas.

trans-unit.source: - <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>, <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>, <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>, and <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> flags on all ACEs in leaf object ACLs are cleared.
trans-unit.target: - <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>, <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>, <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>, e <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>sinalizadores em todas as ACEs na folha do objeto ACLs são desmarcadas.</xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>

trans-unit.source: - ACEs that have an <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags> flag in the absence of the <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> or <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> flag are meaningless; they are removed.
trans-unit.target: -ACEs que têm um <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>sinalizador na ausência da <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>ou <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>sinalizador não fazem sentido; eles serão removidos.</xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>

trans-unit.source: - The <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags> flag in the absence of the <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> or <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> flag can be removed.
trans-unit.target: -A <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>sinalizador na ausência de <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>ou <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags>sinalizador pode ser removido.</xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.InheritanceFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.PropagationFlags>

trans-unit.source: - ACEs that have an <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> value of <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> or <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> in discretionary access control lists (DACLs) are removed.
trans-unit.target: -ACEs que têm um <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>valor <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>ou <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>no controle de acesso discricionário (DACLs) da lista é removida.</xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>

trans-unit.source: - Any audit ACE that does not specify either <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> or <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> is removed.
trans-unit.target: -Qualquer auditoria ACE que não especifica nem <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>ou <xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>é removido.</xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags> </xref:System.Security.AccessControl.AuditFlags>

trans-unit.source: - On DACLs, SystemAudit and SystemAlarm ACEs are removed.
trans-unit.target: -Em DACLs, SystemAudit e SystemAlarm ACEs são removidas.

trans-unit.source: - On system access control lists (SACLs), AccessAllowed and AccessDenied ACEs are removed.
trans-unit.target: -Em listas de controle de acesso do sistema (SACL), AccessAllowed e AccessDenied ACEs são removidas.

trans-unit.source: Canonical order is maintained according to the following algorithm: - Explicit ACEs take precedence over inherited ACEs; this rule applies to both DACLs and SACLs.
trans-unit.target: Ordem canônica é mantida de acordo com o seguinte algoritmo:-ACEs explícitas têm prioridade sobre as ACEs herdadas; Essa regra se aplica a DACLs e SACLs.

trans-unit.source: - In DACLs, among the explicit ACEs, ACEs that deny access take precedence over ACEs that allow access.
trans-unit.target: -Em DACLs, entre as ACEs explícitas, ACEs que negam acesso prevalecerão sobre ACEs que permitam o acesso.

trans-unit.source: For directory object ACLs, the nonobject ACEs come before object ACEs.
trans-unit.target: Para o objeto de diretório ACLs, as ACEs nonobject vêm antes de ACEs de objeto.

trans-unit.source: - All common ACEs take precedence over noncommon ACEs.
trans-unit.target: -Todas as ACEs comuns têm precedência sobre as ACEs noncommon.

trans-unit.source: - Inherited ACEs maintain their relative order after canonicity.
trans-unit.target: -ACEs herdadas mantêm sua ordem relativa após canonicity.

trans-unit.source: - Unrecognized and custom ACEs are disallowed in both DACLs and SACLs.
trans-unit.target: -ACEs não reconhecidas e personalizadas não são permitidas em DACLs e SACLs.

trans-unit.source: - Within contiguous ranges (explicit AccessDenied and AccessAllowed ACEs on DACLs, all explicit ACEs on SACLs), the ACEs are sorted by using the <xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier.CompareTo%2A> methods of the <xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier> objects associated with the ACEs.
trans-unit.target: -Dentro dos intervalos contíguos (AccessDenied explícita e ACEs AccessAllowed em DACLs, todas as ACEs explícitas em SACLs), as ACEs são classificadas usando o <xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier.CompareTo%2A>métodos do <xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier>objetos associados com as ACEs.</xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier> </xref:System.Security.Principal.SecurityIdentifier.CompareTo%2A>

trans-unit.source: Adjacent ACEs are combined, if appropriate.
trans-unit.target: ACEs adjacentes são combinadas, se apropriado.

trans-unit.source: This reduces the size of the ACL without affecting the access control semantics it grants.
trans-unit.target: Isso reduz o tamanho da ACL sem afetar a semântica de controle de acesso que ele concede.
